352
00:23:31.500 --> 00:23:38.430
So, this is Tyre, and this the court.

353
00:23:48.330 --> 00:23:51.230
Here must I kill  King Pericles;

354
00:23:51.230 --> 00:24:00.730
and if I do it not, I am sure to be hanged at home:

355
00:24:00.730 --> 00:24:07.030
'tis dangerous. Well, I perceive

356
00:24:07.030 --> 00:24:11.300
he was a wise fellow, and had good discretion, that,

357
00:24:11.300 --> 00:24:15.030
being bid to ask what he would of the king, desired

358
00:24:15.030 --> 00:24:19.430
he might know none of his secrets: now do I see he

359
00:24:19.430 --> 00:24:23.670
had some reason for't; for if a king bid a man be a

360
00:24:23.670 --> 00:24:26.430
villain, he's bound by the indenture of his oath to

361
00:24:26.430 --> 00:24:30.870
be one! Hush! here come the lords of Tyre.

362
00:24:34.000 --> 00:24:35.670
You shall not need, my fellow peers of Tyre,

363
00:24:35.670 --> 00:24:38.100
Further to question me of your king's departure:

364
00:24:38.100 --> 00:24:40.730
His seal'd commission, left in trust with me,

365
00:24:40.730 --> 00:24:45.670
Doth speak sufficiently he's gone to travel.

366
00:24:45.670 --> 00:24:47.130
How! the king gone!

367
00:24:47.130 --> 00:24:49.830
If further yet you will be satisfied,

368
00:24:49.830 --> 00:24:52.130
Why, as it were unlicensed of your loves,

369
00:24:52.130 --> 00:24:56.370
He would depart, I'll give some light unto you.

370
00:24:56.370 --> 00:24:58.330
Being at Antioch--

371
00:24:58.330 --> 00:24:59.570
What from Antioch?

372
00:24:59.570 --> 00:25:02.400
Royal Antiochus--on what cause I know not--

373
00:25:02.400 --> 00:25:06.430
Took some displeasure at him; at least he judged so:

374
00:25:06.430 --> 00:25:08.100
And doubting lest that he had err'd or sinn'd,

375
00:25:08.100 --> 00:25:11.200
To show his sorrow, he'ld correct himself;

376
00:25:11.200 --> 00:25:13.830
So puts himself unto the shipman's toil,

377
00:25:13.830 --> 00:25:17.930
With whom each minute threatens life or death.

378
00:25:17.930 --> 00:25:20.030
Well, I perceive

379
00:25:20.030 --> 00:25:22.600
I shall not be hang'd now,

380
00:25:22.600 --> 00:25:26.270
But since he's gone, the king's seas must please:

381
00:25:26.270 --> 00:25:30.470
He 'scaped the land, to perish at the sea.

382
00:25:30.470 --> 00:25:36.630
I'll present myself. Peace to the lords of Tyre!

383
00:25:36.630 --> 00:25:39.170
Lord Thaliard from Antiochus is welcome.

384
00:25:39.170 --> 00:25:41.000
From him I come

385
00:25:41.000 --> 00:25:44.370
With message unto princely Pericles;

386
00:25:44.370 --> 00:25:46.870
But since my landing I have understood

387
00:25:46.870 --> 00:25:52.200
Your lord has betook himself to unknown travels,

388
00:25:52.200 --> 00:25:55.930
My message must return from whence it came.

389
00:25:55.930 --> 00:25:57.130
We have no reason to desire it,

390
00:25:57.130 --> 00:26:00.330
Commended to our master, not to us:

391
00:26:00.330 --> 00:26:03.200
Yet, ere you shall depart, this we desire,

392
00:26:03.200 --> 00:26:08.900
As friends to Antioch, we may feast in Tyre.

393
00:26:12.630 --> 00:26:19.630
