1804
02:05:29.830 --> 02:05:33.400
But to have divinity preached there!

1805
02:05:33.400 --> 02:05:34.800
did you ever dream of such a thing?

1806
02:05:34.800 --> 02:05:42.930
No, no. Come, I am for no more bawdy-houses:

1807
02:05:42.930 --> 02:05:46.730
shall's go hear the vestals sing?

1808
02:05:46.730 --> 02:05:49.230
I'll do any thing now that is virtuous;

1809
02:05:49.230 --> 02:05:52.530
but I am out of the road of rutting for ever.

1810
02:06:03.870 --> 02:06:06.900
Well, I had rather than twice the worth of her she

1811
02:06:06.900 --> 02:06:08.570
had ne'er come here.

1812
02:06:08.570 --> 02:06:10.500
Fie, fie upon her! she's able to freeze the god

1813
02:06:10.500 --> 02:06:13.800
Priapus, and undo a whole generation.

1814
02:06:13.800 --> 02:06:16.630
We must either get her ravished, or be rid of her.

1815
02:06:16.630 --> 02:06:18.670
When she should do for clients her fitment, and do me the

1816
02:06:18.670 --> 02:06:20.970
kindness of our profession, she has me her quirks,

1817
02:06:20.970 --> 02:06:24.700
her reasons, her master reasons, her prayers, her knees;

1818
02:06:24.700 --> 02:06:26.230
she would make a puritan of the devil,

1819
02:06:26.230 --> 02:06:28.930
if he should cheapen a kiss of her.

1820
02:06:28.930 --> 02:06:31.200
'Faith, I must ravish her, or she'll disfurnish us

1821
02:06:31.200 --> 02:06:35.570
of all our cavaliers, and make our swearers priests.

1822
02:06:35.570 --> 02:06:38.870
Now, the pox upon her green-sickness for me!

1823
02:06:38.870 --> 02:06:40.970
'Faith, there's no way to be rid on't

1824
02:06:40.970 --> 02:06:44.070
but by the way to the pox.

1825
02:06:49.970 --> 02:06:54.570
Here comes the Lord Lysimachus disguised.

1826
02:06:57.630 --> 02:07:06.370
How now! How a dozen of virginities?

1827
02:07:06.370 --> 02:07:10.170
Now, the gods to-bless your honour!

1828
02:07:10.170 --> 02:07:13.800
I am glad to see your honour in good health.

1829
02:07:14.370 --> 02:07:16.230
You may so; 'tis the well for you that your

1830
02:07:16.230 --> 02:07:25.170
resorters stand upon sound legs. How now!

1831
02:07:25.170 --> 02:07:27.970
wholesome iniquity have you that a man may deal

1832
02:07:27.970 --> 02:07:32.100
withal, and defy the surgeon?

1833
02:07:32.100 --> 02:07:39.730
We have here one, sir, if she would--but there never

1834
02:07:39.730 --> 02:07:41.700
came her like in Mytilene.

1835
02:07:41.700 --> 02:07:44.500
If she'ld but do the deed of darkness,

1836
02:07:44.500 --> 02:07:49.300
thou wouldst say. Your honour knows what 'tis to say

1837
02:07:49.300 --> 02:07:54.200
well enough. Well, call forth, call forth.

1838
02:07:54.200 --> 02:07:56.330
For flesh and blood, sir, white and red, you shall

1839
02:07:56.330 --> 02:08:02.830
see a rose; and she were a rose indeed, if she had but--

1840
02:08:02.830 --> 02:08:05.030
What, prithee?

1841
02:08:05.030 --> 02:08:08.870
O, sir, I can be modest.

1842
02:08:08.870 --> 02:08:11.230
That dignifies the renown of a bawd, no less than it

1843
02:08:11.230 --> 02:08:14.530
gives a good report to a number to be chaste.

1844
02:08:16.430 --> 02:08:20.470
Here comes that which grows to the stalk;

1845
02:08:20.470 --> 02:08:24.300
never plucked yet, I can assure you.

1846
02:08:31.870 --> 02:08:33.730
Is she not a fair creature?

1847
02:08:33.730 --> 02:08:43.670
'Faith, she would serve after a long voyage at sea.

1848
02:08:43.670 --> 02:08:45.630
Well, here's for you: leave us.

1849
02:08:45.630 --> 02:08:48.170
I beseech your honour, give me leave: a word, and

1850
02:08:48.170 --> 02:08:49.900
I'll have done presently.

1851
02:08:49.900 --> 02:08:51.330
I beseech you, do.

1852
02:08:56.330 --> 02:09:02.000
First, I would have you note,

1853
02:09:02.000 --> 02:09:05.430
this is an honourable man.

1854
02:09:05.430 --> 02:09:09.070
I desire to find him so, that I may worthily note him.

1855
02:09:09.070 --> 02:09:11.530
Next, he's the governor of this country,

1856
02:09:11.530 --> 02:09:14.900
and a man whom I am bound to.

1857
02:09:14.900 --> 02:09:18.130
If he govern the country, you are bound to him indeed;

1858
02:09:18.130 --> 02:09:22.530
but how honourable he is in that, I know not.

1859
02:09:22.530 --> 02:09:27.870
Pray you, without any more virginal fencing,

1860
02:09:27.870 --> 02:09:33.830
will you use him kindly? He will line your apron with gold.

1861
02:09:33.830 --> 02:09:38.630
What he will do graciously, I will thankfully receive.

1862
02:09:39.970 --> 02:09:41.370
Ha' you done?

1863
02:09:41.370 --> 02:09:47.130
My lord, she's not paced yet: you must take some

1864
02:09:47.130 --> 02:09:51.400
pains to work her to your manage. Come, we will

1865
02:09:51.400 --> 02:09:55.670
leave his honour and her together. Go thy ways.

1866
02:10:07.330 --> 02:10:10.770
Now, pretty one, how long have you been at this trade?

1867
02:10:10.770 --> 02:10:12.700
What trade, sir?

1868
02:10:12.700 --> 02:10:15.200
Why, I cannot name't but I shall offend.

1869
02:10:15.200 --> 02:10:20.270
I cannot be offended with my trade. Please you to name it.

1870
02:10:20.270 --> 02:10:24.700
How long have you been of this profession?

1871
02:10:24.700 --> 02:10:26.200
E'er since I can remember.

1872
02:10:26.200 --> 02:10:28.070
Did you go to 't so young? Were you a gamester at

1873
02:10:28.070 --> 02:10:29.530
five or at seven?

1874
02:10:29.530 --> 02:10:33.500
Earlier too, sir, if now I be one.

1875
02:10:33.500 --> 02:10:35.700
Why, the house you dwell in proclaims you to be a

1876
02:10:35.700 --> 02:10:38.100
creature of sale.

1877
02:10:38.100 --> 02:10:40.470
Do you know this house to be a place of such resort,

1878
02:10:40.470 --> 02:10:44.430
and will come into 't? I hear say you are of

1879
02:10:44.430 --> 02:10:50.300
honourable parts, and are the governor of this place.

1880
02:10:50.300 --> 02:10:53.070
Why, hath your principal made known unto you who I am?

1881
02:10:53.070 --> 02:10:55.200
Who is my principal?

1882
02:10:55.200 --> 02:10:58.730
Why, your herb-woman; she that sets seeds and roots

1883
02:10:58.730 --> 02:11:06.700
of shame and iniquity. O, you have heard something

1884
02:11:06.700 --> 02:11:10.070
of my power, and so stand aloof for more serious

1885
02:11:10.070 --> 02:11:15.730
wooing. But I protest to thee, pretty one,

1886
02:11:15.730 --> 02:11:18.900
my authority shall not see thee, or else look friendly

1887
02:11:18.900 --> 02:11:24.100
upon thee. Come, bring me to some private place:

1888
02:11:24.100 --> 02:11:25.600
come, come.

1889
02:11:25.600 --> 02:11:27.600
If you were born to honour, show it now;

1890
02:11:27.600 --> 02:11:29.130
If put upon you, make the judgment good

1891
02:11:29.130 --> 02:11:30.600
That thought you worthy of it.

1892
02:11:30.600 --> 02:11:32.670
How's this? how's this? Some more; be sage.

1893
02:11:32.670 --> 02:11:33.800
What reason is there in your justice

1894
02:11:33.800 --> 02:11:37.100
which hath power over all to undo any?

1895
02:11:37.100 --> 02:11:41.500
Take you mine honour and you make a gap into fobidden ground

1896
02:11:41.500 --> 02:11:46.030
Where after all may tread. If then with violence

1897
02:11:46.030 --> 02:11:48.030
you mar this workmanship of heaven

1898
02:11:48.030 --> 02:11:52.030
you will abuse your justice, kill you honour

1899
02:11:52.030 --> 02:11:57.870
and leave me impoverished to the world.

1900
02:11:57.870 --> 02:12:00.300
Why this same house wherein thou live'st

1901
02:12:00.300 --> 02:12:03.770
is a receptacle of all men's sins.

1902
02:12:03.770 --> 02:12:08.330
A nurse of wickedness. How can'st thou be anything

1903
02:12:08.330 --> 02:12:10.730
but naught that dwells within?

1904
02:12:10.730 --> 02:12:15.000
Know you the roof but still will enter here?

1905
02:12:15.000 --> 02:12:17.430
Oh my good lord, if there be fire before me

1906
02:12:17.430 --> 02:12:21.000
must I straightway run to burn myself

1907
02:12:21.000 --> 02:12:24.600
or suppose this house, which two too many

1908
02:12:24.600 --> 02:12:27.730
feels such houses are should be the doctor's patromony

1909
02:12:27.730 --> 02:12:30.200
and the surgeons feeding, follows it that I must needs

1910
02:12:30.200 --> 02:12:38.430
infect myself to maintain them.

1911
02:12:38.430 --> 02:12:43.500
My yet good lord, make me your servant

1912
02:12:43.500 --> 02:12:48.600
and I will obey you. Let me live honest

1913
02:12:48.600 --> 02:12:54.670
and I am content. Honest.

1914
02:12:58.200 --> 02:13:09.830
How now, even in this minute let me die.

1915
02:13:09.830 --> 02:13:11.100
O, that the gods

1916
02:13:11.100 --> 02:13:14.770
Would set me free from this unhallow'd place,

1917
02:13:14.770 --> 02:13:17.800
Though they did change me to the meanest bird

1918
02:13:17.800 --> 02:13:22.900
That flies i' the purer air!

1919
02:13:22.900 --> 02:13:27.870
Now surely this is virtue's image rather virtue's self.

1920
02:13:27.870 --> 02:13:29.930
Come down from heaven awhile to reign on earth

1921
02:13:29.930 --> 02:13:33.300
to teach us what we should be.

1922
02:13:44.570 --> 02:13:47.970
I did not think thou couldst have spoke so well;

1923
02:13:47.970 --> 02:13:51.030
ne'er dream'd thou couldst.

1924
02:13:54.200 --> 02:13:58.430
I hither came with thoughts intemperate, foul and deformed.

1925
02:13:58.430 --> 02:14:02.970
The which your tears have washed, till they are white.

1926
02:14:13.030 --> 02:14:18.770
Your speech has mended my corrupted mind.

1927
02:14:18.770 --> 02:14:21.300
Hold, here's gold for thee:

1928
02:14:21.300 --> 02:14:25.130
Persever in that clear way thou goest,

1929
02:14:25.130 --> 02:14:28.230
And the gods strengthen thee!

1930
02:14:28.230 --> 02:14:29.670
The good gods preserve you!

1931
02:14:29.670 --> 02:14:34.600
Lady, to me the very doors and windows savour vilely.

1932
02:14:34.600 --> 02:14:39.600
Fare thee well. Thou art a piece of virtue,

1933
02:14:39.600 --> 02:14:44.830
and I doubt not but thy training hath been noble.

1934
02:14:46.200 --> 02:14:49.230
Hold, here's more gold for thee.

1935
02:14:52.100 --> 02:14:54.730
A curse upon him, die he like a thief,

1936
02:14:54.730 --> 02:15:04.630
That robs thee of thy goodness!

1937
02:15:04.630 --> 02:15:10.500
If thou dost hear from me, it shall be for thy good.

1938
02:15:13.500 --> 02:15:15.230
I beseech your honour, one piece for me.

1939
02:15:15.230 --> 02:15:18.030
Avaunt, thou damned door-keeper!

1940
02:15:18.030 --> 02:15:21.400
Your house, but for this virgin that doth prop it,

1941
02:15:21.400 --> 02:15:25.230
