2128
02:29:58.630 --> 02:30:00.670
Mark'd he your music?

2129
02:30:00.670 --> 02:30:06.800
No, nor look'd on us.

2130
02:30:12.770 --> 02:30:15.700
See, she will speak to him.

2131
02:30:23.870 --> 02:30:37.930
Hail, sir! my lord, lend ear.

2132
02:30:40.730 --> 02:30:41.730
I am a maid,

2133
02:30:41.730 --> 02:30:43.470
My lord, that ne'er before invited eyes,

2134
02:30:43.470 --> 02:30:48.130
But have been gazed on like a comet: she speaks,

2135
02:30:48.130 --> 02:30:50.330
My lord, that, may be, hath endured a grief

2136
02:30:50.330 --> 02:30:55.070
Might equal yours, if both were justly weigh'd.

2137
02:30:55.070 --> 02:30:57.330
Though wayward fortune did malign my state,

2138
02:30:57.330 --> 02:30:59.100
My derivation was from ancestors

2139
02:30:59.100 --> 02:31:03.930
Who stood equivalent with mighty kings:

2140
02:31:03.930 --> 02:31:06.800
But time hath rooted out my parentage,

2141
02:31:06.800 --> 02:31:08.600
And to the world and awkward casualties

2142
02:31:08.600 --> 02:31:14.030
Bound me in servitude.

2143
02:31:14.030 --> 02:31:18.470
I will desist;

2144
02:31:18.470 --> 02:31:20.470
But there is something glows upon my cheek,

2145
02:31:20.470 --> 02:31:24.330
And whispers in mine ear, 'Go not till he speak.'

2146
02:31:28.170 --> 02:31:35.000
My fortunes--parentage--good parentage--

2147
02:31:35.000 --> 02:31:43.700
To equal mine!--was it not thus? what say you?

2148
02:31:43.700 --> 02:31:45.170
I said, my lord, if you did know my parentage,

2149
02:31:45.170 --> 02:31:48.130
You would not do me violence.

2150
02:31:48.130 --> 02:31:56.270
I do think so. Pray you, turn your eyes upon me.

2151
02:31:56.270 --> 02:32:06.130
You are like something that--What country-woman?

2152
02:32:06.130 --> 02:32:07.900
Here of these shores?

2153
02:32:07.900 --> 02:32:10.770
No, nor of any shores:

2154
02:32:10.770 --> 02:32:12.530
Yet I was mortally brought forth, and am

2155
02:32:12.530 --> 02:32:13.970
No other than I appear.

2156
02:32:13.970 --> 02:32:20.670
I am great with woe, and shall deliver weeping.

2157
02:32:20.670 --> 02:32:24.770
My dearest wife was like this maid, and such a one

2158
02:32:24.770 --> 02:32:34.000
My daughter might have been: my queen's square brows;

2159
02:32:34.000 --> 02:32:37.830
Her stature to an inch; as wand-like straight;

2160
02:32:37.830 --> 02:32:42.330
As silver-voiced; her eyes as jewel-like

2161
02:32:42.330 --> 02:32:49.030
And cased as richly; in pace another Juno;

2162
02:32:49.030 --> 02:32:51.330
Who starves the ears she feeds, and makes them hungry,

2163
02:32:51.330 --> 02:33:01.370
The more she gives them speech. Where do you live?

2164
02:33:01.370 --> 02:33:03.730
Where I am but a stranger:

2165
02:33:03.730 --> 02:33:05.470
From the deck you may discern the place.

2166
02:33:05.470 --> 02:33:08.230
Where were you bred?

2167
02:33:08.230 --> 02:33:11.470
And how achieved you these endowments, which

2168
02:33:11.470 --> 02:33:13.570
You make more rich to owe?

2169
02:33:13.570 --> 02:33:15.170
If I should tell my history, it would seem

2170
02:33:15.170 --> 02:33:18.570
Like lies disdain'd in the reporting.

2171
02:33:18.570 --> 02:33:20.970
Prithee, speak:

2172
02:33:20.970 --> 02:33:24.130
Falseness cannot come from thee; for thou look'st

2173
02:33:24.130 --> 02:33:28.300
Modest as Justice, and thou seem'st a palace

2174
02:33:28.300 --> 02:33:33.200
For the crown'd Truth to dwell in: I will believe thee,

2175
02:33:33.200 --> 02:33:35.070
And make my senses credit thy relation

2176
02:33:35.070 --> 02:33:41.600
To points that seem impossible; for thou look'st

2177
02:33:41.600 --> 02:33:53.230
Like one I loved indeed. What were thy friends?

2178
02:33:53.230 --> 02:33:54.970
Didst thou not say, when I did push thee back--

2179
02:33:54.970 --> 02:33:56.970
Which was when I perceived thee--that thou camest

2180
02:33:56.970 --> 02:33:58.500
From good descending?

2181
02:33:58.500 --> 02:34:00.200
So indeed I did.

2182
02:34:00.200 --> 02:34:03.600
Report thy parentage. I think thou said'st

2183
02:34:03.600 --> 02:34:06.670
Thou hadst been toss'd from wrong to injury,

2184
02:34:06.670 --> 02:34:09.430
And that thou thought'st thy griefs might equal mine,

2185
02:34:09.430 --> 02:34:11.000
If both were open'd.

2186
02:34:11.000 --> 02:34:11.970
Some such thing

2187
02:34:11.970 --> 02:34:14.730
I said, and said no more but what my thoughts

2188
02:34:14.730 --> 02:34:16.170
Did warrant me was likely.

2189
02:34:16.170 --> 02:34:18.870
Tell thy story;

2190
02:34:18.870 --> 02:34:21.570
If thine consider'd prove the thousandth part

2191
02:34:21.570 --> 02:34:23.930
Of my endurance, thou art a man, and I

2192
02:34:23.930 --> 02:34:29.130
Have suffer'd like a girl: yet thou dost look

2193
02:34:29.130 --> 02:34:33.330
Like Patience gazing on kings' graves, and smiling

2194
02:34:33.330 --> 02:34:41.200
Extremity out of act. What were thy friends?

2195
02:34:41.200 --> 02:34:48.130
How lost thou them? Thy name, my most kind virgin?

2196
02:34:48.130 --> 02:34:51.770
Recount, I do beseech thee: come, sit by me.

2197
02:34:57.200 --> 02:35:00.400
My name is Marina.

2198
02:35:00.400 --> 02:35:06.430
O, I am mock'd,

2199
02:35:06.430 --> 02:35:09.400
And thou by some incensed god sent hither

2200
02:35:09.400 --> 02:35:12.700
To make the world to laugh at me.

2201
02:35:12.700 --> 02:35:14.370
Patience, good sir,

2202
02:35:14.370 --> 02:35:16.430
Or here I'll cease.

2203
02:35:16.430 --> 02:35:24.800
Nay, I'll be patient.

2204
02:35:24.800 --> 02:35:26.970
Thou little know'st how thou dost startle me,

2205
02:35:26.970 --> 02:35:30.600
To call thyself Marina.

2206
02:35:30.600 --> 02:35:33.530
The name was given me by one that had some power,

2207
02:35:33.530 --> 02:35:37.800
My father, and a king.

2208
02:35:37.800 --> 02:35:39.700
How! a king's daughter?

2209
02:35:39.700 --> 02:35:42.070
And call'd Marina?

2210
02:35:42.070 --> 02:35:44.800
You said you would believe me;

2211
02:35:44.800 --> 02:35:47.230
But, not to be a troubler of your peace, I will end here.

2212
02:35:47.230 --> 02:35:49.530
But are you flesh and blood?

2213
02:35:49.530 --> 02:35:52.730
Have you a working pulse? and are no fairy?

2214
02:35:58.430 --> 02:36:10.070
Motion! Well; speak on. Where were you born?

2215
02:36:10.070 --> 02:36:13.200
And wherefore call'd Marina?

2216
02:36:13.200 --> 02:36:15.730
Call'd Marina For I was born at sea.

2217
02:36:15.730 --> 02:36:20.800
At sea! what mother?

2218
02:36:20.800 --> 02:36:23.170
My mother was the daughter of a king;

2219
02:36:23.170 --> 02:36:26.130
Who died the minute I was born,

2220
02:36:26.130 --> 02:36:28.000
As my good nurse Lychorida hath oft

2221
02:36:28.000 --> 02:36:30.230
Deliver'd weeping.

2222
02:36:30.230 --> 02:36:35.100
O, stop there a little!

2223
02:36:35.100 --> 02:36:37.130
This is the rarest dream that e'er dull sleep

2224
02:36:37.130 --> 02:36:45.600
Did mock sad fools withal: this cannot be:

2225
02:36:45.600 --> 02:37:00.470
My daughter's buried. Well: where were you bred?

2226
02:37:00.470 --> 02:37:02.130
I'll hear you more, to the bottom of your story,

2227
02:37:02.130 --> 02:37:03.700
And never interrupt you.

2228
02:37:03.700 --> 02:37:06.870
You scorn: believe me, 'twere best I did give o'er.

2229
02:37:06.870 --> 02:37:09.330
I will believe you by the syllable

2230
02:37:09.330 --> 02:37:16.000
Of what you shall deliver. Yet, give me leave:

2231
02:37:16.000 --> 02:37:22.370
How came you in these parts? where were you bred?

2232
02:37:22.370 --> 02:37:26.670
The king my father did in Tarsus leave me;

2233
02:37:26.670 --> 02:37:27.830
Till cruel Cleon, with his wicked wife,

2234
02:37:27.830 --> 02:37:30.100
Did seek to murder me: and having woo'd

2235
02:37:30.100 --> 02:37:32.030
A villain to attempt it, who having drawn to do't,

2236
02:37:32.030 --> 02:37:33.970
A crew of pirates came and rescued me;

2237
02:37:33.970 --> 02:37:37.000
Brought me to Mytilene. But, good sir,

2238
02:37:37.000 --> 02:37:40.800
Whither will you have me? Why do you weep?

2239
02:37:40.800 --> 02:37:43.630
It may be, You think me an impostor:

2240
02:37:43.630 --> 02:37:44.600
no, good faith;

2241
02:37:44.600 --> 02:37:49.000
I am the daughter to King Pericles,

2242
02:37:49.000 --> 02:37:51.470
If good King Pericles be.

2243
02:37:51.470 --> 02:37:59.700
Ho, Helicanus!

2244
02:37:59.700 --> 02:38:01.070
Calls my lord?

2245
02:38:01.070 --> 02:38:02.600
Thou art a grave and noble counsellor,

2246
02:38:02.600 --> 02:38:07.130
Most wise in general: tell me, if thou canst,

2247
02:38:07.130 --> 02:38:11.670
What this maid is, or what is like to be,

2248
02:38:11.670 --> 02:38:13.130
That thus hath made me weep?

2249
02:38:13.130 --> 02:38:14.270
I know not; but

2250
02:38:14.270 --> 02:38:15.970
Here is the regent, sir, of Mytilene

2251
02:38:15.970 --> 02:38:17.170
Speaks nobly of her.

2252
02:38:17.170 --> 02:38:18.530
She would never tell

2253
02:38:18.530 --> 02:38:19.930
Her parentage; being demanded that,

2254
02:38:19.930 --> 02:38:22.870
She would sit still and weep.

2255
02:38:22.870 --> 02:38:33.030
O Helicanus, strike me, royal'd sir;

2256
02:38:33.030 --> 02:38:37.470
Give me a gash, put me to present pain;

2257
02:38:37.470 --> 02:38:43.130
Lest this great sea of joys rushing upon me

2258
02:38:43.130 --> 02:38:44.870
O'erbear the shores of my mortality,

2259
02:38:44.870 --> 02:38:56.370
And drown me with their sweetness. O, come hither,

2260
02:38:56.370 --> 02:39:04.730
Thou that beget'st him that did thee beget;

2261
02:39:04.730 --> 02:39:11.500
Thou that wast born at sea, buried at Tarsus,

2262
02:39:11.500 --> 02:39:16.600
And found at sea again! O Helicanus,

2263
02:39:16.600 --> 02:39:19.830
Down on thy knees, thank the holy gods as loud

2264
02:39:19.830 --> 02:39:30.770
As thunder threatens us: this is Marina.

2265
02:39:30.770 --> 02:39:34.730
What was thy mother's name? tell me but that,

2266
02:39:34.730 --> 02:39:36.330
For truth can never be confirm'd enough,

2267
02:39:36.330 --> 02:39:37.500
Though doubts did ever sleep.

2268
02:39:37.500 --> 02:39:38.730
First, sir, I pray,

2269
02:39:38.730 --> 02:39:39.770
What is your title?

2270
02:39:39.770 --> 02:39:43.130
I am Pericles of Tyre: but tell me now

2271
02:39:43.130 --> 02:39:44.630
My drown'd queen's name, as in the rest you said

2272
02:39:44.630 --> 02:39:47.100
Thou hast been godlike perfect,

2273
02:39:47.100 --> 02:39:49.130
The heir of kingdoms and another like

2274
02:39:49.130 --> 02:39:53.730
To Pericles thy father.

2275
02:39:53.730 --> 02:39:55.030
Is it no more to be your daughter than

2276
02:39:55.030 --> 02:39:57.970
To say my mother's name was Thaisa?

2277
02:39:57.970 --> 02:40:00.530
Thaisa was my mother, who did end

2278
02:40:00.530 --> 02:40:02.300
The minute I began.

2279
02:40:02.300 --> 02:40:14.370
Now, blessing on thee! rise; thou art my child.

2280
02:40:17.170 --> 02:40:22.700
Give me fresh garments. Mine own, Helicanus;

2281
02:40:23.270 --> 02:40:25.130
She is not dead at Tarsus, as she should have been,

2282
02:40:25.130 --> 02:40:28.900
By savage Cleon: she shall tell thee all;

2283
02:40:28.900 --> 02:40:30.800
When thou shalt kneel, and justify in knowledge

2284
02:40:30.800 --> 02:40:35.630
She is thy very princess. Who is this?

2285
02:40:35.630 --> 02:40:37.600
Sir, 'tis the governor of Mytilene,

2286
02:40:37.600 --> 02:40:38.970
Who, hearing of your melancholy state,

2287
02:40:38.970 --> 02:40:40.130
Did come to see you.

2288
02:40:40.130 --> 02:40:42.530
I embrace you.

2289
02:40:42.530 --> 02:40:46.770
Give me my robes. I am wild in my beholding.

2290
02:40:46.770 --> 02:40:53.500
O heavens bless my girl! But, hark, what music?

2291
02:40:53.500 --> 02:40:56.700
Tell Helicanus, my Marina, tell him

2292
02:40:56.700 --> 02:40:58.700
O'er, point by point, for yet he seems to doubt,

2293
02:40:58.700 --> 02:41:02.430
How sure you are my daughter. But, what music?

2294
02:41:02.430 --> 02:41:03.930
(â™ª music)

2295
02:41:03.930 --> 02:41:05.430
My lord, I hear none.

2296
02:41:05.430 --> 02:41:10.170
(â™ª music)

2297
02:41:10.170 --> 02:41:15.830
None!

2298
02:41:19.900 --> 02:41:26.870
The music of the spheres! List, my Marina.

2299
02:41:26.870 --> 02:41:30.070
It is not good to cross him; give him way.

2300
02:41:30.070 --> 02:41:36.670
Rarest sounds! Do ye not hear?

2301
02:41:36.670 --> 02:41:39.530
Music, my lord, I hear.

2302
02:41:40.170 --> 02:41:44.670
Most heavenly music!

2303
02:41:45.730 --> 02:41:50.630
It nips me unto listening, and thick slumber

2304
02:41:50.630 --> 02:41:58.600
Hangs upon mine eyes: let me rest.

2305
02:42:01.800 --> 02:42:06.430
A pillow for his head:

2306
02:42:06.430 --> 02:42:08.270
So, leave him.

2307
02:42:17.830 --> 02:42:20.970
Well, my companion friends,

2308
02:42:20.970 --> 02:42:23.300
If this but answer to my just belief,

2309
02:42:23.300 --> 02:42:25.530
I'll well remember you.

2310
02:42:39.630 --> 02:42:44.800
My temple stands in Ephesus: hie thee thither,

2311
02:42:44.800 --> 02:42:50.100
And do upon mine altar sacrifice.

2312
02:42:50.100 --> 02:42:54.600
There, when my maiden priests are met together,

2313
02:42:54.600 --> 02:42:56.770
Before the people all,

2314
02:42:56.770 --> 02:43:02.000
Reveal how thou at sea didst lose thy wife:

2315
02:43:02.000 --> 02:43:04.700
To mourn thy crosses, with thy daughter's, call

2316
02:43:04.700 --> 02:43:09.100
And give them repetition to the life.

2317
02:43:09.100 --> 02:43:14.430
Perform my bidding, or thou livest in woe;

2318
02:43:14.430 --> 02:43:20.630
Do it, and happy; by my silver bow!

2319
02:43:20.630 --> 02:43:26.630
Awake, and tell thy dream.

2320
02:43:26.630 --> 02:43:34.300
Celestial Dian, goddess argentine,

2321
02:43:34.300 --> 02:43:37.930
I will obey thee.

2322
02:43:49.800 --> 02:43:55.470
Helicanus!

2323
02:43:55.470 --> 02:43:57.570
Sir?

2324
02:43:57.570 --> 02:44:00.070
My purpose was for Tarsus, there to strike

2325
02:44:00.070 --> 02:44:02.830
The inhospitable Cleon; but I am

2326
02:44:02.830 --> 02:44:05.170
For other service first: toward Ephesus

2327
02:44:05.170 --> 02:44:09.500
Turn our blown sails; eftsoons I'll tell thee why.

2328
02:44:12.400 --> 02:44:14.430
Shall we refresh us, sir, upon your shore,

2329
02:44:14.430 --> 02:44:16.070
And give you gold for such provision

2330
02:44:16.070 --> 02:44:17.170
As our intents will need?

2331
02:44:17.170 --> 02:44:20.200
Sir, With all my heart; and, when you come ashore,

2332
02:44:20.200 --> 02:44:23.570
I have another suit.

2333
02:44:26.170 --> 02:44:29.130
You shall prevail,

2334
02:44:29.130 --> 02:44:32.030
Were it to woo my daughter; for it seems

2335
02:44:32.030 --> 02:44:35.030
You have been noble towards her.

2336
02:44:35.030 --> 02:44:40.000
Sir, lend me your arm.

2337
02:44:40.000 --> 02:44:45.630
Come, my Marina.

2338
02:45:09.700 --> 02:45:13.270
Now our sands are almost run;

2339
02:45:13.270 --> 02:45:17.800
More a little, and then dumb.

2340
02:45:17.800 --> 02:45:19.500
This, my last boon, give me,

2341
02:45:19.500 --> 02:45:22.870
For such kindness must relieve me,

2342
02:45:22.870 --> 02:45:24.330
That you aptly will suppose

2343
02:45:24.330 --> 02:45:29.400
What pageantry, what feats, what shows,

2344
02:45:29.400 --> 02:45:30.600
What minstrelsy, and pretty din,

2345
02:45:30.600 --> 02:45:32.200
The regent made in Mytilene

2346
02:45:32.200 --> 02:45:36.100
To greet the king. So he thrived,

2347
02:45:36.100 --> 02:45:38.170
That he is promised to be wived

2348
02:45:38.170 --> 02:45:40.800
To fair Marina; but in no wise

2349
02:45:40.800 --> 02:45:42.830
Till he had done his sacrifice,

2350
02:45:42.830 --> 02:45:46.030
As Dian bade: whereto being bound,

2351
02:45:46.030 --> 02:45:49.470
The interim, pray you, all confound.

2352
02:45:49.470 --> 02:45:54.070
In feather'd briefness sails are fill'd,

2353
02:45:54.070 --> 02:45:57.630
And wishes fall out as they're will'd.

2354
02:45:57.630 --> 02:46:01.030
At Ephesus, the temple see,

2355
02:46:01.030 --> 02:46:04.270
Our king and all his company.

2356
02:46:05.530 --> 02:46:07.130
That he can hither come so soon,

2357
02:46:07.130 --> 02:46:10.970
Is by your fancy's thankful doom.

2358
02:46:19.400 --> 02:46:24.770
Hail, Dian! to perform thy just command,

2359
02:46:24.770 --> 02:46:27.970
I here confess myself the king of Tyre;

2360
02:46:27.970 --> 02:46:29.570
Who, frighted from my country, did wed

2361
02:46:29.570 --> 02:46:33.670
At Pentapolis the fair Thaisa.

2362
02:46:33.670 --> 02:46:38.900
At sea in childbed died she, but brought forth

2363
02:46:38.900 --> 02:46:41.930
A maid-child call'd Marina; who, O goddess,

2364
02:46:41.930 --> 02:46:47.800
Wears yet thy silver livery. She at Tarsus

2365
02:46:47.800 --> 02:46:51.430
Was nursed with Cleon; who at sixteen years

2366
02:46:51.430 --> 02:46:54.470
He sought to murder: but her better stars

2367
02:46:54.470 --> 02:46:57.830
Brought her to Mytilene; 'gainst whose shore

2368
02:46:57.830 --> 02:47:00.300
Riding, her fortunes brought the maid aboard us,

2369
02:47:00.300 --> 02:47:04.430
Where, by her own most clear remembrance, she

2370
02:47:04.430 --> 02:47:08.230
Made known herself my daughter.

2371
02:47:11.570 --> 02:47:20.570
Voice and favour!

2372
02:47:20.570 --> 02:47:30.870
You are, you are--O royal Pericles!

2373
02:47:30.870 --> 02:47:32.170
She dies! help, gentlemen!

2374
02:47:32.170 --> 02:47:33.800
To the lady.

2375
02:47:37.430 --> 02:47:39.270
Noble sir,

2376
02:47:39.270 --> 02:47:41.770
If you have told Diana's altar true,

2377
02:47:41.770 --> 02:47:44.770
This is your wife.

2378
02:47:44.770 --> 02:47:47.900
Reverend appearer, no;

2379
02:47:47.900 --> 02:47:50.130
I threw her overboard with these very arms.

2380
02:47:50.130 --> 02:47:53.630
Upon this coast, I warrant you.

2381
02:47:53.630 --> 02:47:57.570
'Tis most certain.

2382
02:47:57.830 --> 02:48:03.630
O, she's but o'erjoy'd.

2383
02:48:03.630 --> 02:48:07.530
Early one blustering morn this lady was

2384
02:48:07.530 --> 02:48:13.270
Thrown upon this shore. I oped the coffin,

2385
02:48:13.270 --> 02:48:17.270
Found her rich jewels; recover'd her,

2386
02:48:17.270 --> 02:48:20.070
and placed her here in Diana's temple.

2387
02:48:20.970 --> 02:48:22.470
May we see them?

2388
02:48:22.470 --> 02:48:24.400
Great sir, they shall be brought you to my house,

2389
02:48:24.400 --> 02:48:29.600
Whither I invite you. Look, Thaisa is recovered.

2390
02:48:29.600 --> 02:48:33.570
O, let me look!

2391
02:48:33.570 --> 02:48:36.200
If he be none of mine, my sanctity

2392
02:48:36.200 --> 02:48:38.970
Will to my sense bend no licentious ear,

2393
02:48:38.970 --> 02:48:45.400
But curb it, spite of seeing. O, my lord,

2394
02:48:45.400 --> 02:48:53.430
Are you not Pericles? Like him you spake,

2395
02:48:53.430 --> 02:48:59.470
Like him you are: did you not name a tempest,

2396
02:48:59.470 --> 02:49:01.400
A birth, and death?

2397
02:49:01.400 --> 02:49:05.930
The voice of dead Thaisa!

2398
02:49:05.930 --> 02:49:11.300
That Thaisa am I, supposed dead

2399
02:49:11.300 --> 02:49:13.570
And drown'd.

2400
02:49:13.570 --> 02:49:15.870
Immortal Dian!

2401
02:49:15.870 --> 02:49:17.370
Now I know you better.

2402
02:49:17.370 --> 02:49:19.070
When we with tears parted Pentapolis,

2403
02:49:19.070 --> 02:49:21.600
The king my father gave you such a ring.

2404
02:49:21.600 --> 02:49:32.530
This, this: no more, you gods! your present kindness

2405
02:49:32.530 --> 02:49:38.900
Makes my past miseries sports: you shall do well,

2406
02:49:38.900 --> 02:49:43.600
That on the touching of her lips I may

2407
02:49:43.600 --> 02:49:50.000
Melt and no more be seen. O, come, be buried

2408
02:49:50.000 --> 02:49:53.870
A second time within these arms.

2409
02:49:54.500 --> 02:50:00.000
My heart Leaps to be gone into my mother's bosom.

2410
02:50:00.000 --> 02:50:04.630
Look, who kneels here! Flesh of thy flesh, Thaisa;

2411
02:50:04.630 --> 02:50:07.830
Thy burden at the sea, and call'd Marina

2412
02:50:07.830 --> 02:50:10.600
For she was yielded there.

2413
02:50:10.600 --> 02:50:20.630
Blest, and mine own!

2414
02:50:20.630 --> 02:50:26.170
Blest, and mine own!

2415
02:50:26.170 --> 02:50:31.530
Hail, madam, and my queen!

2416
02:50:31.530 --> 02:50:34.300
I know you not.

2417
02:50:34.300 --> 02:50:37.000
You have heard me say, when I did fly from Tyre,

2418
02:50:37.000 --> 02:50:38.530
I left behind an ancient substitute:

2419
02:50:38.530 --> 02:50:39.900
Can you remember what I call'd the man?

2420
02:50:39.900 --> 02:50:42.700
I have named him oft.

2421
02:50:42.700 --> 02:50:44.400
'Twas Helicanus then.

2422
02:50:44.400 --> 02:50:45.830
Still confirmation:

2423
02:50:45.830 --> 02:50:51.230
Embrace him, dear Thaisa; this is he.

2424
02:50:51.230 --> 02:50:53.200
Now do I long to hear how you were found;

2425
02:50:53.200 --> 02:50:56.430
How possibly preserved; and who to thank,

2426
02:50:56.430 --> 02:51:00.270
Besides the gods, for this great miracle.

2427
02:51:00.270 --> 02:51:05.900
Lord Cerimon, my lord; this man,

2428
02:51:05.900 --> 02:51:08.500
Through whom the gods have shown their power; that can

2429
02:51:08.500 --> 02:51:11.200
From first to last resolve you.

2430
02:51:11.200 --> 02:51:12.700
Reverend sir,

2431
02:51:12.700 --> 02:51:14.430
The gods can have no mortal officer

2432
02:51:14.430 --> 02:51:16.770
More like a god than you. Will you deliver

2433
02:51:16.770 --> 02:51:20.970
How this dead queen re-lives?

2434
02:51:20.970 --> 02:51:21.900
I will, my lord.

2435
02:51:21.900 --> 02:51:24.200
Beseech you, first go with me to my house,

2436
02:51:24.200 --> 02:51:26.730
Where shall be shown you all was found with her;

2437
02:51:26.730 --> 02:51:28.470
How she came placed here in the temple;

2438
02:51:28.470 --> 02:51:31.070
No needful thing omitted.

2439
02:51:40.230 --> 02:51:45.000
Pure Dian, I bless thee for thy vision!

2440
02:51:45.000 --> 02:51:48.870
And will offer night-oblations to thee.

2441
02:51:51.700 --> 02:51:55.300
Thaisa, This prince,

2442
02:51:55.300 --> 02:51:59.100
the fair-betrothed of your daughter,

2443
02:51:59.100 --> 02:52:03.030
Shall marry her at Pentapolis. And now,

2444
02:52:03.030 --> 02:52:06.270
This ornament

2445
02:52:06.270 --> 02:52:09.700
Makes me look dismal will I clip to form;

2446
02:52:09.700 --> 02:52:12.800
And what these many years no razor touch'd,

2447
02:52:12.800 --> 02:52:15.670
To grace thy marriage-day, I'll beautify.

2448
02:52:19.800 --> 02:52:22.970
Lord Cerimon hath letters of good credit, sir,

2449
02:52:22.970 --> 02:52:26.000
My father's dead.

2450
02:52:27.830 --> 02:52:32.770
Heavens make a star of him! Yet there, my queen,

2451
02:52:32.770 --> 02:52:35.230
We'll celebrate their nuptials, and ourselves

2452
02:52:35.230 --> 02:52:38.900
Will in that kingdom spend our following days:

2453
02:52:38.900 --> 02:52:43.670
Our son and daughter shall in Tyrus reign.

2454
02:52:43.670 --> 02:52:45.870
Lord Cerimon, we do our longing stay

2455
02:52:45.870 --> 02:52:52.200
To hear the rest untold: sir, lead's the way.

2456
02:53:09.930 --> 02:53:12.800
In Antiochus and his daughter you have heard

2457
02:53:12.800 --> 02:53:17.230
Of monstrous lust the due and just reward:

2458
02:53:17.230 --> 02:53:21.100
In Pericles, his queen and daughter, seen,

2459
02:53:21.100 --> 02:53:24.170
Although assail'd with fortune fierce and keen,

2460
02:53:24.170 --> 02:53:28.170
Virtue preserved from fell destruction's blast,

2461
02:53:28.170 --> 02:53:33.600
Led on by heaven, and crown'd with joy at last:

2462
02:53:33.600 --> 02:53:35.370
In Helicanus may you well descry

2463
02:53:35.370 --> 02:53:39.970
A figure of truth, of faith, of loyalty:

2464
02:53:39.970 --> 02:53:42.030
In reverend Cerimon there well appears

2465
02:53:42.030 --> 02:53:48.030
The worth that learned charity aye wears:

2466
02:53:48.030 --> 02:53:50.570
For wicked Cleon and his wife, when fame

2467
02:53:50.570 --> 02:53:53.170
Had spread their cursed deed, and honour'd name

2468
02:53:53.170 --> 02:53:57.570
Of Pericles, to rage the city turn,

2469
02:53:57.570 --> 02:54:04.600
That he and his they in his palace burn;

2470
02:54:04.600 --> 02:54:06.630
The gods for murder seemed so content

2471
02:54:06.630 --> 02:54:13.370
To punish; although not done, but meant.

2472
02:54:13.370 --> 02:54:20.700
So, on your patience evermore attending,

2473
02:54:20.700 --> 02:54:28.370
New joy wait on you! Here our play has ending.

2474
